        <!-- /ãƒ¡ã‚¤ãƒ³ã‚³ãƒ³ãƒ†ãƒ³ãƒ„ã‚³ãƒ³ãƒ†ãƒŠ (æ—¥æœ¬èª) --><!-- è‹±èªã‚»ã‚¯ã‚·ãƒ§ãƒ³ --><a id="english" class="relative -top-20 section-anchor"></a> <!-- ã‚¢ãƒ³ã‚«ãƒ¼ä½ç½®èª¿æ•´ --><div class="white-card p-6 sm:p-10 space-y-12 mt-16">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">English Section</h2>

            <section>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Important</h3>
                <p class="text-red-800">
                    License has changed
                </p>
            </section>

            <p class="text-gray-600">
                **FoliaPhantom-extra** is a manual patching utility designed to run legacy Bukkit, Spigot, and Paper plugins on a Folia server (the multi-threaded version of PaperMC).
            </p>

            <section>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">ğŸš€ Key Features</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-4 list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Bytecode Transformation Technology:</strong> Directly analyzes plugin class files and rewrites <code class="text-blue-700">BukkitScheduler</code> calls to use Folia's <code class="text-blue-700">RegionScheduler</code> and <code class="text-blue-700">AsyncScheduler</code>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Automatic <code class="text-blue-700">plugin.yml</code> Patching:</strong> Automatically adds or corrects the <code class="text-blue-700">folia-supported: true</code> flag in the target plugin's <code class="text-blue-700">plugin.yml</code>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Broad Scheduler Compatibility:</strong> Supports major and legacy scheduler methods, properly converting both synchronous and asynchronous tasks.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Terrain & World Gen Compatibility:</strong> Attempts to wrap calls to <code class="text-blue-700">ChunkGenerator</code> and synchronous <code class="text-blue-700">createWorld</code> to work within Folia's asynchronous environment.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">âš™ï¸ Installation and Usage</h3>
                <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-4 text-gray-700">
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Install FoliaPhantom-extra:</strong> Download the latest <code class="text-blue-700">FoliaPhantom-extra.jar</code> from the <a href="https://github.com/MARVserver/FoliaPhantom/releases" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 section-anchor">Releases page</a>.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Generate Directories:</strong> Start the server once to create <code class="text-blue-700">input</code> and <code class="text-blue-700">output</code> inside <code class="text-blue-700">plugins/FoliaPhantom-extra/</code>.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Place Target JARs:</strong> Stop the server. Move plugin JARs into the <code class="text-blue-700">input</code> directory.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Run the Patcher:</strong> Start the server again. <code class="text-blue-700">FoliaPhantom-extra</code> will process JARs in the <code class="text-blue-700">input</code> directory.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Retrieve Patched JARs:</strong> Patched files are saved to the <code class="text-blue-700">output</code> directory. Original files are deleted upon successful processing.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-gray-900">Install the Patched Plugin:</strong> Move the patched JAR from <code class="text-blue-700">output</code> to the main <code class="text-blue-700">plugins</code> folder.</li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">âš ï¸ Limitations & Disclaimers</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-4 list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700">
                    <li><strong class="text-red-600">Risk of Synchronous World Generation:</strong> Synchronously calling time-consuming methods like <code class="text-blue-700">createWorld</code> may cause temporary server freezes (Watchdog warnings).</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-red-600">NMS/CB Dependencies:</strong> Compatibility is not guaranteed for plugins relying directly on <code class="text-blue-700">net.minecraft.server</code> (NMS) or <code class="text-blue-700">org.bukkit.craftbukkit</code> (CB) code.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-red-600">Advanced Class-loading:</strong> May conflict with security plugins or those performing complex class-loader manipulations.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-red-600">Not a 100% Guarantee:</strong> This plugin does not guarantee all plugins will work. Please report issues on <a href="https://github.com/MARVserver/FoliaPhantom/issues" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 section-anchor">GitHub Issues</a>.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

        </div>
